{
  "stem": "15540.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in our family, my father and his brothers kind of divided who would take care of who.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So some people were more able to take care of themselves than others.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my father kind of took in charge one uncle and his, and his wife, because they were more nervous people, that he felt that they would need help.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so they, they came with us and fled with us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So that the day that we finally, when we left Copenhagen, which was on the, on the 30th of September, my aunt and uncle and their two children came along with us on, on a train, which we--",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Gunner ?] and Kis Markus.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they actually, my, my uncle had a very good friend who had already been active in the, in the opposition and, and among the freedom fighters, and he accompanied us and tried to help us make arrangements to find a boat at that time.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was with us on the train down to, to the part of Denmark that where we fled from, which was the southern part of Denmark, not very conveniently located to Sweden, but they thought because it wasn't, that the Germans wouldn't think of it and it would be safer.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Most people fled directly across the, the sound between Denmark and Sweden, which at one point was only a 20-minute boat ride, and at best, like, you know, maybe an hour, an hour and a half.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Where we were was considerably bigger distance.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so when it didn't go smoothly, it was a very bad way to go.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we left-- I mean, during the day.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
